  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: This package binds two requirements whose acceptance thresholds are mutually exclusive at the COU operating point — Requirement A mandates RH < 1.0 relative to predicate, while Requirement B mandates RH ≤ 0.85 for all flow-speed combinations exceeding 4 L/min at 3000 RPM, the exact operating point used in this assessment. A model result of RH = 0.92 satisfies Requirement A but violates Requirement B; conversely, any result satisfying B automatically satisfies A, but the converse does not hold, creating an inconsistency that allows the assessment to be declared Accepted under one requirement while failing the other.",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-dual-threshold",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case",
